               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-157-person1556">
                  JOSEPH 
                  MARTINDALE
               <interp inst="t18270913-157-person1556" type="surname" value="MARTINDALE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-157-person1556" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-157-person1556" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 1st of September I was in <placeName id="t18270913-157-crimeloc896">Southampton-street, in the Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-157-crimeloc896" type="placeName" value="Southampton-street, in the Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-157-crimeloc896" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-157-off894 t18270913-157-crimeloc896"></join>, between eleven and twelve o'clock at night; a person stopped me in the street, and asked if I had lost any thing. I then missed my handkerchief - I did not see the prisoner till he was in custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-157-person1557">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WHITTINGHAM
               <interp inst="t18270913-157-person1557" type="surname" value="WHITTINGHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-157-person1557" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-157-person1557" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner following Mr. Martindale, who had two ladies on his arm. I saw the prisoner make several attempts to get the handkerchief, and, at the top of Southampton-street, he got it out - I rushed forward, and he threw it behind him - I seized him, and another person picked it up for me. I got a person to overtake Mr. Martindale, and told him of it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. This officer seized me, and said,"D-n you, I have got you at last." The gentleman<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182709130094"></xptr>never gave charge of me - I was standing at the top of the street when the gentleman and ladies came by - I moved to let them pass, but had not touched the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-157-verdict897" type="verdictDescription">
